  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0daf \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0dbb\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2 - \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dc3\u0da7\u0db1\u0da7 \u0d91\u0db1 \u0d85\u0dba\u0d9c\u0dda \u0db1\u0dcf\u0db8 \u0dba\u0ddd\u0da2\u0db1\u0dcf \u0d9a\u0dd0\u0db3\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Parliament will meet today - the President will call for nominations of those coming to the fray",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Parliament is scheduled to meet today to call for nominations from the candidates for the election to be held tomorrow in Parliament for the election of a President.",
        "With the resignation of Gotabaya Rajapaksa from the presidency, Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe has constitutionally become the Acting President.",
        "Accordingly, nominations are being invited from members of parliament today to appoint a president for the vacant post of president.",
        "Acting President Ranil Wickramasinghe, opposition leader Sajith Premadama, Anura Kumara Dissanayake of the National People's Power and Dallas Alahapperuma representing the independent group of the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna have already announced that they will join the polls as candidates."
      ],
      "title_ents": [
